    "answer": "The bug is a classic state mutation issue. In `useCartState.mjs`, `addItem` creates `next` as a reference to `state` (`next = state`), then mutates it directly with `next.items.push(item)`. This violates the test's immutability check (line 9 expects `state.items` to remain `[]`).\n\nFix by creating a new object and copying items:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFix verified. The test now passes:\n\n```\n# tests 1\n# pass 1\n# fail 0\n```\n\nChanged `next = state` to `next = { items: [...state.items], total: 0 }` to create a proper immutable copy of the state.",
